title: Boston & Maine Railroad Trail Tunnel - West Entrance
poiData_title: Boston & Maine Railroad Trail Tunnel - West Entrance
poiData_description: The tunnel was built in 1903 as part of the Boston & Maine Railroad when tracks had to be rerouted due to the creation of the Wachusett Reservoir. The tunnel was decommissioned in 1958 and now serves as part of a hiking trail.
